HEADWORD: Clarendon
<hw>Clar"en*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A style of type
having a narrow and heave face. It is made in all sizes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This line is in nonpareil Clarendon.</note>⟦br⟧
